# Google Ads API Configuration
# Follow these steps to set up Google Ads API integration:

# 1. Create a Google Ads API application at https://developers.google.com/google-ads/api/docs/first-call/overview
# 2. Get your Developer Token from Google Ads API Center
# 3. Set up OAuth2 credentials and get refresh token
# 4. Find your Customer ID in Google Ads account

# Google Ads API Credentials
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_ID=your_oauth2_client_id_here
GOOGLE_ADS_CLIENT_SECRET=your_oauth2_client_secret_here
GOOGLE_ADS_REFRESH_TOKEN=your_refresh_token_here
GOOGLE_ADS_DEVELOPER_TOKEN=your_developer_token_here
GOOGLE_ADS_CUSTOMER_ID=your_customer_id_here

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your actual credentials
# 2. Never commit actual credentials to version control
# 3. The Customer ID should be in format: 123-456-7890 (without dashes in the actual value)
# 4. Developer Token must be approved by Google for production use
# 5. For testing, you can use a test account with limited functionality

# Note: Without these credentials, the system will fall back to simulated campaign data
